      "Using frequency-domain NIRS during the Digit Symbol Substitution Test, adults with sickle cell disease showed lower baseline tissue oxygen saturation than controls and a larger post-task decline despite similar accuracy — suggesting cognitive demand further challenges cerebral oxygen delivery in SCD.",
  },
  {
    title:
      "The potential of using a hemodynamic signal as a biomarker of cognitive load in sickle cell disease",
    authors:
      "S. Roy, N. Mossazghi, E. Bulger, J. Lin, C. Saber, B. Shinn-Cunningham, J. M. Kainerstorfer, J. Z. Xu, S. Wood",
    venue: "SfNIRS",
    year: 2024,
    type: "Abstract",
